subSubSection.paragraph:
More specific features separating
Lodinus
from other Blapstinina genera are listed below:

Notibius

(Southwest US and 
Mexico
): Lacks developed flight wings. Dense setal fimbriae on lateral margin of pronotum. Foretibiae expanded and slightly curved (narrow and straight in 

Lodinus

). Aedeagus curvature sinuate in lateral view (
Iwan 2004
).

Ulus : Pronotum
and elytra covered with setae and bearing lateral fimbriae. Foretibia dilated, ending in a distal ‘tooth’ (
Lumen et al . 2019
). Appears to be only blapstinine with enlarged, membranous field on basal portion of aedeagal tegmen (
Lumen et al . 2019
).
